description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/17842/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'marine fish', in the Global geography.;This market does not contain any transportation, as it is included in the market for the specific products. This is a generic market for any wild marine fish and includes many species. Marine fish  is any fish captured in open sea and landed for primarily human consumption. Various fishing methods are employed and are documented in the respective producing activity datasets.   More information are found in the product information of marine fish.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'marine fish',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of  marine fish', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
